Package model

Class Index

java.lang.Object
model.Index
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class Index
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
Represents an index belonging to a single course. Students enrolled in a course will be divided up into the course's various indexes.

    • lessons

      private java.util.HashMap<LessonType,​java.util.ArrayList<TimeSlot>> lessons
      Represents the lessons that are conducted by this index, with each lesson having a LessonType and a TimeSlot.

      Stored in a hashmap data structure that contains the LessonTypes as its keys, with each LessonType key pointing to a list of TimeSlots of that particular LessonType.

    • Index

      public Index​(Course course, int index_number, int max_capacity)
      Constructor for Index. Each Index is linked to only 1 Course.
      Parameters:
      course - The Course object that this Index belongs to.
      index_number - This Index's index number.
      max_capacity - This Index's maximum number of students that it can take in.
